          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The thin self-supporting metallic foils of 64Ni",
                " ( e5 = 22 mm) were prepared by electrolytic deposition",
                "Its isotopic composition was 58Ni (9.8%), 60Ni(6.9%),",
                "61Ni (0.5%), 62Ni (5.0%), 64Ni (77.8%); the admixture",
                "of Cu amounted to 0.012% by weight. The surface density",
                "of the foils ranged between 3 and 8 mg/cm2. Two stacks",
                "of 64Ni foils, each containing up to 12 samples.",
                "The first stack contained a number of high purity",
                "copper foils with the surface densities between 4.3 and",
                "4.7 mg/cm2 and a few aluminium foils in the sequences",
                "Cu-Ni and Ni-Al. The copper foils served as beam energy",
                "absorbers, beam flux monitors and also allowed",
                "cx-particle beam energy control along the stack. The",
                "aluminium foils were used as beam energy absorbers",
                "and catchers of the escaping residual nuclei.",
                "The second stack contained aluminium foils inserted",
                "between 64Ni foils and a single copper foil was used",
                "for the beam current measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
