              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Ga-67 produced in Cu monitor foil partly escaped to",
                "Ni foil.",
                "For separation of 67Ga and 67Cu the authors used the",
                "difference in branching ratios of the strongest",
                "gamma-transitions of those radionuclides",
                " (both decaying to stable Zn-67). The ratio of",
                "the adopted gamma-ray abundances of the radiative",
                "transitions 93.3 and 91.3 keY equals to 2.3",
                "for 67Cu decay and 12.4 for 67Ga decay, while the ratio",
                "for 93.3 and 184.6keV transition abundances equals to",
                "0.33 and 1.85 for 67Cu and 67Ga decays, respectively."
              ]
            }
